This paper is primarily focused on industrial intrusion detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the analysis of process data, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Matrix Profiles for anomaly detection suggests a potential application of time series analysis (cs.SI). Finally, the application of one-class classifiers could also fall under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
